Thailand Stocks: Central Pattana, PTT Exploration, UOB Kay Hian

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-05-25T09:49:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/thailand-stock-movers-ptt-ptt-exploration-uob-kay-hian.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Thailand trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index fell 8.70, or 0.8 percent, to 1,055.54, the
lowest since May 23.  Oil companies :  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s biggest energy
company, dropped 1.1 percent to 348 baht, the lowest close since
May 6.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  , the
country’s only publicly traded oil explorer, lost 1.5 percent to
170.5 baht.  Crude oil dropped in New York after an industry-funded
report showed gasoline supplies surged in the U.S., the world’s
largest crude user, signaling demand may falter.  Central Pattana Pcl (CPN)  , the largest shopping mall
developer, declined 2.6 percent to 28.5 baht, the most in a
week. Central Pattana plans to spend 43.5 billion baht ($1.43
billion) between 2011 and 2014 to renovate existing stores and
develop new outlets, Naparat Sriwanvit, the company’s finance
manager, told investors in Bangkok today. The company will
finance the construction with loans, surplus cash and sales of a
real estate investment trust, she said.  UOB Kay Hian Securities (Thailand) Pcl (UOBKH TB), a
brokerage unit of Singapore-based UOB-Kay Hian Holdings Ltd.,
jumped 7.1 percent to 3.64 baht, the steepest advance since Jan.
11. The brokerage plans to acquire United Securities Public Co.
for 942 million baht ($31 million), its parent said in a
statement to the  Singapore Exchange  today. UOB Kay Hian offered
to buy United Securities’ shares at 5.58 baht each. Shares of
 United Securities Pcl (US)   were suspended from trading by the
stock exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  